The paper deals with understanding the learning and generalization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper proposes a model of linear F-Principle dynamics to predict the learning results of two-layer ReLU neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses an optimization formulation to estimate the generalization error bound, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in discussing the Frequency Principle and its biases. The paper's focus on understanding the implicit biases of deep neural networks also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
